Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, half the @Shawarma Spice Blend{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest in the next step), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and crisp, ~{18-20%minutes}. (It's natural for chickpeas to pop a bit while roasting.)

While chickpeas roast, dice @whole wheat pitas{2} into 1-inch pieces. Toss on a second baking sheet with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{3%tsp}, remaining Shawarma Spice, salt, and pepper.

Toast on middle rack until browned and crispy, ~{7-9%minutes}.

Let cool at least ~{5%minutes} before adding to salad in step 4.

Pat @salmon{10%oz} dry with paper towels and season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add salmon (skin sides down). Cook salmon until skin is crisp and fish is almost cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Meanwhile, halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Trim and quarter @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Greek vinaigrette{3%oz} with @sugar{1%tsp}.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together @spinach{5%oz}, tomatoes, cucumber, ¾ of the toasted pitas, half the chickpeas, half the @feta cheese{½%cup}, and half the vinaigrette. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide salad between shallow bowls or plates. Top with remaining roasted chickpeas, remaining feta, remaining vinaigrette, and as much of the remaining toasted pitas as you like. Serve.